@node Main "Quador - Documentation"

                              'Quador' 1.0

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Quador' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} where you rotate 4 neighbouring
tiles to make alignments of 4 coloured tiles or more of the same
type horizontally, vertically or both at the same time. The more
tiles of the same type there are, the more points you get. A thing
to watch for is the number of remaining tiles of any type. If less
than 4 tiles of a type are present, the game ends... unless some
'neutral blocks' are present on the game board...

  A particularity of the game is that when you line up 4 or more
tiles of the same type, they are then removed and are replaced with
small square neutral blocks. This can help, especially if there are
few of one type of tiles, as it will allow you to continue to
play. As the blocks 'grow' one size for each move you make, when
they reach their maximum size, they are replaced with new coloured
tiles.

  Have fun!

