@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Quador" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher and a Workbench with at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on a board of 8 by 8 spaces filled with
various coloured tiles. The idea is to make alignments of at least
4 tiles of the same type horizontally, vertically or both at the
same time. The more tiles of the same type there are, the more
points you get: 4 tiles give 1 point, 5 tiles give 5 points, 6
tiles give 25 points and 7 tiles give 125 points.

  To play, click on a tile, except on a tile that is on the
rightmost column or on the lowest row. This will make a rotation,
in a clockwise manner, of the 4 neighbouring tiles: the clicked
tile, the tile located at the right, the tile located one row below
at right and the tile located under the clicked tile.

  When at least 4 tiles of the same type are aligned, they are then
removed from the board and are replaced by small square 'neutral'
blocks. These blocks will 'grow' one size larger each time you
click and make a rotation of 4 tiles. When the square blocks reach
their maximum size (after 5 moves), these blocks are replaced by
new coloured tiles.

  Beware when the number of tiles of one type is below 4, as that
would end the game, unless some neutral blocks are present on the
game board. When there are less than 6 tiles of one type, an
indicator, located at the right of the game board, displays which
type of tile it is and how many tiles are remaining.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

